T1	Participants 58 101	patients with mild to moderate hypertension
T2	Participants 104 212	A total of 2242 patients with mild to moderate hypertension (diastolic pressure 95-120 mmHg) were randomised
T3	Participants 309 595	Patients were identified who: (a) met the blood pressure (BP) criteria for first-dose hypotension (sitting or standing systolic BP < 100 mmHg, or a fall in systolic BP > or = 20 mmHg on standing); (b) had symptoms suggestive of hypotension; and (c) met the BP criteria and had symptoms.
